Pre-Game Insights: The New York Mets and Chicago White Sox will send Sean Manaea and Garrett Crochet, respectively, out to start when the two clubs square off on Sunday at Guaranteed Rate Field, at 2:10 p.m. ET.
The Mets’ 4.10 team ERA ranks 15th across all league pitching staffs.
The White Sox have pitched to a 4.88 ERA this season, which ranks 29th in baseball.
The game will be broadcast on NBC Sports Networks and can be live-streamed on Fubo.
